body:
@leifwalsh, we're going to have to figure out how the REPL works for 2.11 in terms of how class files are shipped over to Spark clusters. Previously, this was done with an entirely separate HTTP server, but it looks like they might have merged that in to the SparkContext's class server for 2.11.

I'm sure that there are several tests that are broken by this and will need to have Scala 2.10 and Scala 2.11 versions in the same manner that this branch provides implementations of the Scala interpreter class for 2.10 and 2.11.

@lbustelo, did we want this done before the first binary release?

@lbustelo, we've gotten this to pass, but accidentally clobbered it. We really, really, REALLY need to raise the Akka timeout so we stop hitting these false failures.

Passing run of the tests: https://travis-ci.org/apache/incubator-toree/builds/118560171

So, merge it when you've got time. We've also manually run through the magics in a notebook.

@chipsenkbeil Take a look at what I ended up doing in https://github.com/lbustelo/incubator-toree/blob/ShareSqlContext/kernel/src/main/scala/org/apache/toree/boot/layer/ComponentInitialization.scala#L131. 

My goal was to surface the weird dependency between ScalaInterpreter and Kernel out to the ComponentInit level. That way, Kernel is pretty clean of the weirdness.

I also move `start` to be something that is call explicitly for ScalaInterpreter. Don't like how it ends up getting called, but I think that is now major scope creep for this PR. I have no issues with cleaning up the rest of the Interpreter interface and lifecycle as a separate PR.
